Change History:

# 1.4.1 - 2011-01-07 ###

  Minor change(s):
    - Changed the shortcuts from actual links to text files (easier to back up)
    - Changed the link to the current theme to a text file

# 1.4 - 2011-01-05 ###

  Major change(s):
    - Created a test suite for testing compatibility with non-Debian distros

  Minor change(s):
    - Shortcut list file is now deleted and recreated once when first displayed
    - Separated out command functions (sc-commands.sh)
    - Separated out messages (sc-messages.sh)
    - Separated out path declarations (sc-paths.sh)
    - Added licence notices (GPLv3) to source code

# 1.3.2 - 2010-11-22 ###

  Minor change(s):
    - Standardized alternative command format: scadd, scdelete, scexport, scget,
      schelp, sclabel, sclist, screname, scupdate, sctheme

# 1.3.1 - 2010-11-21 ###

  New feature(s):
    - Partial shortcut name matching

  Minor change(s):
    - Added ./docs/CHANGELOG file (this document)

# 1.3.0 - 2010-11-20 ###

  New feature(s):
    - Theme support (light and dark themes included)

  Minor change(s):
    - Re-organize file and directory structure (final configuration!)

# 1.2.2 - 2010-11-19 ###

  Minor change(s):
    - Move the help text to a separate file
    - Write the short-cut list to a separate file (improves response)
    - Re-organize file and directory structure

# 1.2.1 - 2010-10-02 ###

  Minor change(s):
    - Enhanced command 'sc -a NAME TARGET LABEL'

# 1.2.0 - 2010-10-02 ###

  New features(s):
    - New command 'sc -g NAME' - return path for shortcut

# 1.1.0 - 2010-10-01 ###

  New feature(s):
    - New command 'sc -l NAME LABEL' - add label to shortcut
    - New command 'sc -r NAME NEWNAME' - rename shortcut

  Minor change(s):
    - Export now converts hyphens and full-stops (periods) to underscore when
      creating BASH variable name
    - Path text is now displayed below the short-cut. If a label exists then
      the path is not shown
    - Added colour to shortcuts list output
    - Added colour to export list output

# 1.0.1 - 2010-06 ###

  Minor change(s):
    - Command 'sc' with no options now lists shortcuts
    - Command 'sc -a' with no options will create shortcut name from the
      current directory

# 1.0 - 2010-05 ###

   - First release
